  "body": "There is currently a bug with the docker shim checkpoint file when the file is corrupt that can cause the kubelet to not be able to stop a sandbox.\r\n\r\nThe issue occurs because `buildCNIRuntimeConf()` modifies the error from `GetPodPortMappings()` as it propagates the error:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/network/cni/cni.go#L303 \r\n\r\nThe corrupted checkpoint file should be removed by the higher level:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockershim/docker_sandbox.go#L200\r\n\r\nBut because the error has been modified, this is not run and treated as an unhandled error, continuously blocking `StopPodSandbox()`.\r\n\r\nResults in continuous `could not retrieve port mappings: checkpoint is corrupted` errors.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
